		<td><b>224/239 lines test ROM?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'd like to run a test ROM on a real SNES, which can switch between 224 and 239-line modes. I want to see exactly which scanlines are the extra ones in 239-line mode. Does anyone know whether such a program already exists? Or is that information already known? I'm thinking about the scanlines as output to the TV, not necessarily those from the point of view of the SNES program.<br /><br />In other words, I'd like to determine exactly how many scanlines above and below the normal 224-line active area are used in 239-line mode.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
