		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">ARM9 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You're welcome, yes I threw it together in C, feel free to share it. Out of curiosity, what's the problem with it in snes9x gtk?</div>When the mode changes from 239 to 224 lines, the image in the lower lines remains there. To show the problem enable &quot;Use overscanned height&quot; in preferences then load your test ROM. Press and hold B to use 239-line mode. Release B to return to 224-line mode, and the bottom of the display (where lines 224-238 were) still contains that green colour.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
